column18: 01/18/2004: An explosion occurred on the Ethiopian-Djibouti train near Daasbyo, Djibouti. Six passengers were injured in the attack. As a result of the incident, the government decided to suspend the Ethiopian-Dijbouti route. No group claimed responsibility for the blast.
